                    <span>As others have pointed out this first person/third person thing is quite hilarious.  After about the second or third time you come across this "Eller" fellow who seems to be always on the scene and always right, you look back and see his name on the cover.  But the funnier one is every now and then you can almost hear Jennifer Edstrom saying "and then mommy saved the day again ..."
<br />
<br />However I did give it more than the minimum, because I do think there is value in getting a perspective from what it looked like from the front line.  I did finish the book, and I think I got some insight into Microsoft.  
<br />
